column1: 118000;instagram;2018-12-10 21:35:50;FALSE;"for years after i was molested and raped
when my parents found out about the molestation
column2: i was asked what i did to encourage it. i was 10 years old when it started. it's no wonder that i never told anyone when i was raped when i was 13.  my mind's process buried the memory in the back of my fear cabinet and didn't reference it for nearly 30 years.

column1: every time i watched a news story describing an assault on a child
column2: i was instantly outraged. i wanted every child predator punished and harshly. i would say things like 'he should be shot and pissed on' or 'they should put him in jail and throw away the key'

column1: the file in my fear cabinet gained intensity every time it was referenced and my negative perspectives about the men who hurt children was projected onto every man i encountered - both intentionally and unintentionally.
i took on a warrior attitude thinking i was helping myself stay safe and protected
column2: but i didn't understand how the law of attraction actually worked. my warrior attitude invited the very type of disrespectful men into my life - exactly who i wanted to avoid. this ensured my already rigid perspectives would be validated and reinforced.

column1: the only way to stop this cycle was to learn how to rewrite the files in the filing cabinets of my mind and forgive the men who harmed me.

it took me decades to heal. don't let that be your story. choose you over your anger. choose you over holding on to the resentments.  choose you over waiting for an apology that you won't get and choose you over the desire for revenge.

column1: writing a memoir deepened my compassion for others. sure
column3: i had been taught compassion by my parents. but writing memoir introduced me to a whole new authenticity of compassion. writing memoir involves deep introspection and interrogation
column4: and like any practice that exercises those muscles
column5: it makes you look at an experience from all points of view
column6: including the views and backstories of the characters who once hurt you. be it through abandonment. negligence. betrayal. physical
column8: or emotional violence. i expected to feel anger while revisiting those chapters and characters of my life. and i did feel anger. but the most prominent and lasting emotion was empathy. compassion. and sympathy.

column1: all of us were born as children. innocent and full of trust in the world. then
column2: it is through nonchalant or deliberate wounds that our faith is fractured. we become the love or the pain that is taught to us. in this there lives an invitation and potential for empathy
column4: forgiveness toward life and those who wound. in this there exists proof that every human is but a sum of choices
column8: we all hold the power and possibility to heal
column11: and evolve. we can choose love.

column1: 118067;instagram;2018-12-10 20:09:39;FALSE;70 years ago we adopted the universal declaration of human rights yet we still face huge human rights challenges worldwide and in the uk. sexual violence is a violation of a persons human rights. even the justice system in the uk which seeks to protect those rights openly violates other rights of survivors. at present the criminal justice system protects the perpetrator whilst the victim is violated over and over again by the invasive procedures of the cps. the violation of privacy and collection of data from victims is unlawful. the justice system is failing survivors and leaving them without justice or support. the current procedures used by the cps breach data protection and violate human rights law. we have got to fight for a fully just victim centred justice system. â€˜injustice anywhere is a threat to justice everywhereâ€™ #martinlutherking #humanrights #bigbrotherwatch #sistersuncut #thegeminiproject #endthesilence #believesurvivors #westandwithsurvivors #stopdefendingcriminals #supportsurvivors #endviolenceagainstwomen #justicenow #timeforchange #metoomvt #hearmetoo #timesup #metoo #justicewillprevail #standup4humanrights #humanrightsday #udhr70 #fuckthecps #survivorsnotsuspects #supportnotsuspicion #sistersunited #wedemandjustice #endsexualviolence;;en;#martinlutherking

column1: 118200;instagram;2018-12-10 18:15:05;FALSE;"to overcome is to overpower... to defeat... to prevail.

column2: after years of abuse... & i overcame.

column1: i lost a loved one to suicide causing mass hysteria within my mind... & i overcame.
i found myself in a toxic relationship resulting in an eating disorder and attempted suicide... & i overcame.
i almost became homeless... & i overcame.
all of these things i used to use as reasons for why i could never see the other side of who i could be - the other side of what life could look like.
i used to feel shame for my weakness and that alone kept me from my greatest strength - overcoming.

this year we wanted to shed light on a very important issue & the theme of this yearâ€™s #16days - how to deal with domestic abuse in the workplace.

this year we wanted to shed light on a very important issue & the theme of this yearâ€™s #16days - how to deal with domestic abuse in the workplace.
70% of those who experienced domestic violence were targeted at work. the majority of people who experience domestic violence are employed.
this is why standtall works with employers to help them address domestic abuse and support their staff in getting the help they might need. â€¢

this is why standtall works with employers to help them address domestic abuse and support their staff in getting the help they might need. â€¢

today these principles continue to be the beacon of our society and the basis of our daily actions. letâ€™s ensure humanityâ€™s values are always upheld and never abandoned.

column1: 118254;instagram;2018-12-10 17:52:58;FALSE;"i've read so many opinions about the murder of grace millane. the 21 year old british backpacker killed in nz the night before her 22nd birthday. she was last seen in a hotel near a bar i've frequented for years and her body was found near where so many of my friends live and where so many of us go in summer to the numerous beaches and look out spots. my nz family are devistated that she survived months in south america then died in nz. i'm a kiwi writing this in liverpool. in the last 14 months i've been to 18 countries
column2: some of which alone and have attended more than one multi day festival alone too. i've read articles saying it's not her fault
column3: i've read others saying it's not safe for woman to be out alone or travel alone. this is my opinion on the matter.

column1: after #metoo i kept seeing 'it's not all men' and seeing my male friends upset about being tarnished with the same brush.
but i can say with absolute certainty that all women. everyone of your girlfriends
column7: daughters - all of us have had to think twice about outfits
column9: which way to walk home from the bus stop or train station (even if that ally way cuts out 15 mins walking and it's raining and we need to pee)
column10: we've walked with our keys threaded through our fingers
column11: not had headphones on at night
column12: made our friends text us when we got home and us them. we've shrugged off catcalls
column14: not worn that mini skirt that makes us feel like a super model because tonight you just can't be bothered dealing with all the arse grabs and cat calls that come with it. we order drinks in bottles so we can keep our thumbs over the top
column15: we take our drinks into toilets so they aren't drugged... in fact we do these things so often we don't even think about it anymore

column1: it's not all men but the problems are still with men. what are you doing to make your woman safer? parents what are you teaching your boys about consent and bodily awareness?
rip grace. one day i hope we know a world where it is safe to be a woman and we don't need to worry about these things anymore.

column1: 118365;instagram;2018-12-10 16:01:15;FALSE;"have you tried over and over and over again to loose the same 10
column3: 50 pounds?  have you found weight loss success in the past and then hit a plateau that seems as big as mt. everest because no matter what you do
column4: old habits keep creeping back in?  have you entered the holiday season telling yourself several times that ""this year will be different"" and yet you've already given up or had a major setback?

column1: well my friends......welcome to the table.  with me.  yep
column3: but this time i know exactly why.  fear.  you see
column4: i've had a lot on my plate the last 6 months and i let a few old habits creep back in when things got scary.  i've accomplished a ton of wonderful things personally
column6: i let my focus slide on my nutrition and i let fear hold me back in workouts because my old self was reminding me of what happened last time.

column1: last time i was at my peak of health
column2: having lost over 135lbs and entering competitive competitions for fun
column3: was when i was diagnosed with #achalasia and my world turned upside down.

column1: the last 1.5 years has been hard
column2: but i have never given up.  i have sat at the same weight almost this whole time
column3: but training for a new work position got the best of me the last few trips away.  so
column4: it's back to the focus board and i'm practicing what i preach to my clients who have been so successful in loosing over 100lbs between them!

column1: we focus on 2lbs at a time.  we drink more water (at lest 1/2 your weight in oz/day). we drink water before meals.  we eat veggies as our first bite off our plate.  we track everything that goes into our mouths
column2: and we recognize that food is either fuel or poison.  you can make small changes every day to help loose those extra pounds.  the first step is really recognizing you're uncomfortable
column3: and knowing regret kinda sucks.  big.  focus on 2lbs at a time
column5: and you can begin where you are at today.  not tomorrow. today.  who's with me in building their 2lbs board this week?  post it and tag me in it so i can celebrate with you as you move along in your journey!";;en;#Achalasia;;;;;0;;tigerstripesearned;Bri | Female Empowerment Coach;;0;False;1;0;0;31;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/ce70207528820fd1b8012a89aa43d17b/5D14ABFD/t51.2885-15/e35/43695412_388045628406363_5095811569397007335_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"have you tried over and over and over again to loose the same 10

column4: it is back to the focus board and i am practicing what i preach to my clients who have been so successful in loosing over 100lbs between them!

column1: we focus on 2lbs at a time.  we drink more water (at lest 1/2 your weight in oz/day). we drink water before meals.  we eat veggies as our first bite off our plate.  we track everything that goes into our mouths
column2: and we recognize that food is either fuel or poison.  you can make small changes every day to help loose those extra pounds.  the first step is really recognizing you are uncomfoable
column3: and knowing regret kinda sucks.  big.  focus on 2lbs at a time
column5: and you can begin where you are at today.  not tomorrow. today.  who's with me in building their 2lbs board this week?  post it and tag me in it so i can celebrate with you as you move along in your journey!";tried loose 10

column1: *the name of this body of work is entitled ""me too in art history"". i have re-created three famous art pieces; â€œare you jealous?â€ by paul gauguin
column3: and â€œself-portraitâ€ by chuck close.  they are all mixed-media art quilts using scraps of fabric
column5: and various sewing techniques.  they have a satirical side which illustrates the sexual misconducts of the three original artists.  the women in the paintings are not represented as the artists originally intended
column6: but i  approached them in a way to represent their point of view while being the victims of sexual assault.  the questions at hand:  should we be celebrating the artworks from people who have a history of sexual deviance at the hands of others?  do the work of other artists accused of questionable conduct need to be recontextualized?

column1: *the name of this body of work is entitled ""me too in art history"". i have re-created three famous art pieces; â€œare you jealous?â€ by paul gauguin
column3: and â€œself-portraitâ€ by chuck close.  they are all mixed-media art quilts using scraps of fabric
column5: and various sewing techniques.  they have a satirical side which illustrates the sexual misconducts of the three original artists.  the women in the paintings are not represented as the artists originally intended
column6: but i  approached them in a way to represent their point of view while being the victims of sexual assault.  the questions at hand:  should we be celebrating the artworks from people who have a history of sexual deviance at the hands of others?  do the work of other artists accused of questionable conduct need to be recontextualized?

column1: 118533;instagram;2018-12-10 12:13:41;FALSE;"today i got the chance to hang out with a few grade 8 students at american international school of lesotho(aisl)  we celebrated #humanrightsday by talking about different articles in the universal declaration of human rights and how we can each make the world a better place by protecting these rights.
the pupils also had a few questions about how they can become activists for social justice in their communities. all in all it was a great session
column2: we even ran out of time and couldn't discuss everything.

column1: very grateful to mr. mark brookes who is director at aisl for the invite. even more happy to hear how aware those kids were about their human rights and responsibilities towards their communities and the rest of the world.
looking forward to the next session
column2: maybe we will talk bodily autonomy next.

i  been trying really hard to keep up a brave face lately + be positive +  adress serious topics but...these panphobics are really getting to me + its only making my seasonal depression worse. i try and tell myself to toughen up +  i should be used to bring bullied for being pan because i always have been but i don't wanna be used to it. i shouldn't have to be used to it.
i love myself for being pansexual and that's who i am.

during the abuse i pushed away my sexuality  so they would stop hurting me.. i went numb + venomous + i wanted to die with every fider of my soul.. but i found strength in who i was then  i got the courage to rebel and i loved myself and my sexuality ever since because it gave me strength when all my strength was ripped from me.
so it hurts a lot to hear such horrid things. it hurts on a level they'll never be able to understand. i'm trying to do my best i really am its just so hard right now. it hurts a lot. ~ witchy

showered and just started to cry. i couldnt quite understand why. that's just not like me to get emotional over things i can not understand. i felt like shit!

column1: it wasn't until i was drifting off to sleep that it clicked.

for those of you who have been following me you'll know that this year i came out about my past traumas with sexual abuse. what happened made my body react even though my mind couldn't realize it. it is obviously still attempting to block my past out.
i could choose to continue to feel terrible about what had happened to me
column2: but instead i choose to feel empowered! i am happy to have quickly recognized the trigger and i do not allow my past to control my present.

column1: i get to take back my power today! today is amazing! i am happy
column2: heslthy and safe!  and i appreciate what happened last night
column3: because it brings me closer to meeting the man that i will feel safe and comfortable with.

column1: 118675;instagram;2018-12-10 09:29:46;FALSE;"""one day i had to go to mirigama
column2: and i was a little confused as to which bus to take
column3: so i asked a nice looking old person. a few minutes into waiting
column4: he got on the same bus and sat next to me. i wasn't too alarmed yet
column5: and he even confirmed my bus-stop with the driver for me. after the bus started
column6: he began making small talk. he then fell asleep
column8: began to lean into me. eventually he was leaning on me the entire time. i woke him up for his stop
column9: but he kept sitting next to me. suddenly
column10: he wanted to exchange contact information
column11: and that's when i noticed the red flag. i kept saying no
column12: but he pushed even more. he then told me that he developed feelings for me
column13: and that he wanted to be even close to me. i kept saying no
column14: and i froze out of shock. he got more aggressive
column15: and said he missed his stop for me. he also said he knew where i lived
column16: and would follow me home. my stop finally came
column17: and i stood up to leave. but he kept blocking me
column18: so i jumped over him and tried to run for it. but he grabbed my ankle. i shook him off and ran for my life onto another bus. once i got home
column19: i told my family about my encounter. they told me it was normal
column20: and that i shouldn't travel alone. i decided to never use public transport ever again after that"" - opula

column1: if you witness sexual harassment in public transport: intervene. speak up. be the change.

column1: 118718;instagram;2018-12-10 05:53:59;FALSE;"this is the face of a women trying so damn hard to keep it together. so iâ€™m going to tell a little pinch of my past to do with systematically falling into one domestic violent relationship to the next. when i was 11 years old i spent a lot of time at one of my bestfriends houses & we were just happy innocent kids looking for ways to entertain ourselves in a small country town with the population of around 500 people.. or even less back then. anyways her older brother started to show an attraction too me but not in any type of healthy ways
i wonâ€™t go into details as i myself donâ€™t want to have to relive it again. but he raped me
column2: and that was the end of my friendship with his sister and basically i had no idea what the hell had even happened too me until 3 years later on when i was sexually attacked by an unknown man walking home from the shops late one afternoon. i was taken to hospital & treated for trauma etc. strange thing is that now at 26yrs old i only really remember laying in a hospital bed with my dad complaining about having to pay the ambulance bill
column3: my brain has kind of blocked out the rest somehow. only gods knows for what reason after these events
column4: i started to only have an attraction for older men someone who i believed would protect me and help me be safe at all times
column5: little did i know i was setting myself up for the worst ride of my life. i felt depersonalised i didnâ€™t know myself and started to rely on who ever i was seeying at the time to create my happiness. which was always shattered since i never had a steady
column6: official relationship with anyone until i turned 18.  then i thought i found the love of my life... the one man every single person i know told me too stay away from
column7: even i had sirens going off in my head but chose to ignore them
column11: everything i could of hoped for
column12: it was so intense and i fell so damn hard
column13: but only 2 weeks into our relationship he started playing mind games with me
column14: accusing me of sleeping with his mates which of coarse i didnâ€™t i was too blinded by love to even see another males existence. tbc
